347 static void MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_reportFxn
348 (
349  DPM_Report reportType,
350  uint32_t instanceId,
351  int32_t errCode,
352  uint32_t arg0,
353  uint32_t arg1
354 )
355 {
356 
357  /* Only errors are logged on the console: */
358  if (errCode != 0)
359  {
360  /* Error: Detected log on the console and die all errors are FATAL currently. */
361  System_printf ("Error: DPM Report %d received with error:%d arg0:0x%x arg1:0x%x\n",
362  reportType, errCode, arg0, arg1);
363  DebugP_assert (0);
364  }
365 
366  /* Processing further is based on the reports received: This is the control of the profile
367  * state machine: */
368  switch (reportType)
369  {
370  case DPM_Report_IOCTL:
371  {
372  /*****************************************************************
373  * DPC has been configured without an error:
374  * - This is an indication that the profile configuration commands
375  * went through without any issues.
376  *****************************************************************/
377  DebugP_log1("DSSApp: DPM Report IOCTL, command = %d\n", arg0);
378  break;
379  }
380  case DPM_Report_DPC_STARTED:
381  {
382  /*****************************************************************
383  * DPC has been started without an error:
384  * - notify sensor management task that DPC is started.
385  *****************************************************************/
386  DebugP_log0("DSSApp: DPM Report start\n");
387  gMmwDssMCB.dpmStartEvents++;
388  /* every sensor start should cause 2 DPM start events due to distributed domain */
389  break;
390  }
391  case DPM_Report_NOTIFY_DPC_RESULT:
392  {
393  /*****************************************************************
394  * DPC Results have been passed:
395  * - This implies that we have valid profile results which have
396  * been received from the profile.
397  *****************************************************************/
398 
399  break;
400  }
401  case DPM_Report_NOTIFY_DPC_RESULT_ACKED:
402  {
403  /*****************************************************************
404  * DPC Results have been acked:
405  * - This implies that MSS received the results.
406  *****************************************************************/
407 
408  break;
409  }
410  case DPM_Report_DPC_ASSERT:
411  {
412  DPM_DPCAssert* ptrAssert;
413 
414  /*****************************************************************
415  * DPC Fault has been detected:
416  * - This implies that the DPC has crashed.
417  * - The argument0 points to the DPC assertion information
418  *****************************************************************/
419  ptrAssert = (DPM_DPCAssert*)arg0;
420  System_printf ("DSS Exception: %s, line %d.\n", ptrAssert->fileName,
421  ptrAssert->lineNum);
422  break;
423  }
424  case DPM_Report_DPC_STOPPED:
425  {
426  /*****************************************************************
427  * DPC has been stopped without an error:
428  * - This implies that the DPC can either be reconfigured or
429  * restarted.
430  *****************************************************************/
431  DebugP_log0("DSSApp: DPM Report stop\n");
432  gMmwDssMCB.dpmStopEvents++;
433  /* every sensor stop should cause 2 DPM stop events due to distributed domain
434  Its safe to start printing logs on the first event as RF/RadarSS chirp/frame are already stopped */
435  if (gMmwDssMCB.dpmStopEvents % 2 == 1)
436  {
437  MmwDemo_sensorStopEpilog();
438  }
439  break;
440  }
441  case DPM_Report_DPC_INFO:
442  {
443  /* Currently chain does not use this feature. */
444  break;
445  }
446  default:
447  {
448  DebugP_assert (0);
449  break;
450  }
451  }
452  return;
453 }

503  void MmwDemo_updateObjectDetStats
504 (
505  DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats *currDpcStats,
506  MmwDemo_output_message_stats *outputMsgStats
507 )
508 {
509  static uint32_t prevInterFrameEndTimeStamp = 0U;
510 
511  /* Calculate interframe proc time */
512  outputMsgStats->interFrameProcessingTime =
513  (currDpcStats->interFrameEndTimeStamp - currDpcStats->interFrameStartTimeStamp)/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ; /* In micro seconds */
514 
515  outputMsgStats->interChirpProcessingMargin = currDpcStats->interChirpProcessingMargin/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ;
516 
517  /* Calculate interFrame processing Margin for previous frame, but saved to current frame */
518  outputMsgStats->interFrameProcessingMargin =
519  (currDpcStats->frameStartTimeStamp - prevInterFrameEndTimeStamp - currDpcStats->subFramePreparationCycles)/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ;
520 
521  prevInterFrameEndTimeStamp = currDpcStats->interFrameEndTimeStamp;
522 }

537 static int32_t MmwDemo_copyResultToHSRAM
538 (
539  MmwDemo_HSRAM *ptrHsramBuffer,
540  DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *result,
541  MmwDemo_output_message_stats *outStats
542 )
543 {
544  uint8_t *ptrCurrBuffer;
545  uint32_t totalHsramSize;
546  uint32_t itemPayloadLen;
547 
548  /* Save result in HSRAM */
549  if(ptrHsramBuffer == NULL)
550  {
551  return -1;
552  }
553 
554  /* Save result in HSRAM */
555  if(result != NULL)
556  {
557  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult);
558  memcpy((void *)&ptrHsramBuffer->result, (void *)result, itemPayloadLen);
559  }
560  else
561  {
562  return -1;
563  }
564 
565  /* Save output Stats in HSRAM */
566  if(outStats != NULL)
567  {
568  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_stats);
569  memcpy((void *)&ptrHsramBuffer->outStats, (void *)outStats, itemPayloadLen);
570  }
571 
572  /* Set payload pointer to HSM buffer */
573  ptrCurrBuffer = &ptrHsramBuffer->payload[0];
574  totalHsramSize = MMWDEMO_HSRAM_PAYLOAD_SIZE;
575 
576  /* Save ObjOut in HSRAM */
577  if(result->objOut != NULL)
578  {
579  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudCartesian) * result->numObjOut;
580  if((totalHsramSize- itemPayloadLen) > 0)
581  {
582  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)result->objOut, itemPayloadLen);
583 
584  ptrHsramBuffer->result.objOut = (DPIF_PointCloudCartesian *)ptrCurrBuffer;
585  ptrCurrBuffer+= itemPayloadLen;
586  totalHsramSize -=itemPayloadLen;
587  }
588  else
589  {
590  return -1;
591  }
592  }
593 
594  /* Save ObjOutSideInfo in HSRAM */
595  if(result->objOutSideInfo != NULL)
596  {
597  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo) * result->numObjOut;
598  if((totalHsramSize- itemPayloadLen) > 0)
599  {
600  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)result->objOutSideInfo, itemPayloadLen);
601  ptrHsramBuffer->result.objOutSideInfo = (DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo *)ptrCurrBuffer;
602  ptrCurrBuffer+= itemPayloadLen;
603  totalHsramSize -=itemPayloadLen;
604  }
605  else
606  {
607  return -1;
608  }
609  }
610 
611  /* Save DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats in HSRAM */
612  if(result->stats != NULL)
613  {
614  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats);
615  if((totalHsramSize- itemPayloadLen) > 0)
616  {
617  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)result->stats, itemPayloadLen);
618  ptrHsramBuffer->result.stats = (DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats *)ptrCurrBuffer;
619  ptrCurrBuffer+= itemPayloadLen;
620  totalHsramSize -=itemPayloadLen;
621  }
622  else
623  {
624  return -1;
625  }
626  }
627 
628  /* Save compRxChanBiasMeasurement in HSRAM */
629  if(result->compRxChanBiasMeasurement != NULL)
630  {
631  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPU_AoAProc_compRxChannelBiasCfg);
632  if((totalHsramSize- itemPayloadLen) > 0)
633  {
634  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)result->compRxChanBiasMeasurement, itemPayloadLen);
635  ptrHsramBuffer->result.compRxChanBiasMeasurement = (DPU_AoAProc_compRxChannelBiasCfg *)ptrCurrBuffer;
636  ptrCurrBuffer+= itemPayloadLen;
637  totalHsramSize -=itemPayloadLen;
638  }
639  else
640  {
641  return -1;
642  }
643  }
644 
645  return totalHsramSize;
646 }

659 static void MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_dpmTask(UArg arg0, UArg arg1)
660 {
661  int32_t retVal;
662  DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *result;
663  volatile uint32_t startTime;
664 
665  while (1)
666  {
667  /* Execute the DPM module: */
668  retVal = DPM_execute (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle, &resultBuffer);
669  if (retVal < 0) {
670  System_printf ("Error: DPM execution failed [Error code %d]\n", retVal);
671  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
672  }
673  else
674  {
675  if ((resultBuffer.size[0] == sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult)))
676  {
677  result = (DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *)resultBuffer.ptrBuffer[0];
678 
679  /* Get the time stamp before copy data to HSRAM */
680  startTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
681 
682  /* Update processing stats and added it to buffer 1*/
683  MmwDemo_updateObjectDetStats(result->stats,
684  &gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.subFrameStats[result->subFrameIdx]);
685 
686  /* Copy result data to HSRAM */
687  if ((retVal = MmwDemo_copyResultToHSRAM(&gHSRAM, result, &gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.subFrameStats[result->subFrameIdx])) >= 0)
688  {
689  /* Update interframe margin with HSRAM copy time */
690  gHSRAM.outStats.interFrameProcessingMargin -= ((Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime)/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ);
691 
692  /* Update DPM buffer */
693  resultBuffer.ptrBuffer[0] = (uint8_t *)&gHSRAM.result;
694  resultBuffer.ptrBuffer[1] = (uint8_t *)&gHSRAM.outStats;
695  resultBuffer.size[1] = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_stats);
696 
697  /* YES: Results are available send them. */
698  retVal = DPM_sendResult (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle, true, &resultBuffer);
699  if (retVal < 0)
700  {
701  System_printf ("Error: Failed to send results [Error: %d] to remote\n", retVal);
702  }
703  }
704  else
705  {
706  System_printf ("Error: Failed to copy processing results to HSRAM, error=%d\n", retVal);
707  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
708  }
709  }
710  }
711  }
712 }

723 static void MmwDemo_dssInitTask(UArg arg0, UArg arg1)
724 {
725  int32_t errCode;
726  Task_Params taskParams;
727  DPM_InitCfg dpmInitCfg;
728  DPC_ObjectDetection_InitParams objDetInitParams;
729 
730  /*****************************************************************************
731  * Driver Init:
732  *****************************************************************************/
733 
734  /* Initialize the Mailbox */
735  Mailbox_init(MAILBOX_TYPE_DSS);
736 
737  /*****************************************************************************
738  * Driver Open/Configuraiton:
739  *****************************************************************************/
740  /* Initialize EDMA */
741  MmwDemo_edmaInit(&gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj, DPC_OBJDET_DSP_EDMA_INSTANCE);
742 
743  /* Use instance 1 on DSS */
744  MmwDemo_edmaOpen(&gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj, DPC_OBJDET_DSP_EDMA_INSTANCE);
745 
746  /*****************************************************************************
747  * Initialization of the DPM Module:
748  *****************************************************************************/
749  memset ((void *)&objDetInitParams, 0, sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_InitParams));
750 
751  objDetInitParams.L3ramCfg.addr = (void *)&gMmwL3[0];
752  objDetInitParams.L3ramCfg.size = sizeof(gMmwL3);
753  objDetInitParams.CoreL2RamCfg.addr = &gDPC_ObjDetL2Heap[0];
754  objDetInitParams.CoreL2RamCfg.size = sizeof(gDPC_ObjDetL2Heap);
755  objDetInitParams.CoreL1RamCfg.addr = &gDPC_ObjDetL1Heap[0];
756  objDetInitParams.CoreL1RamCfg.size = sizeof(gDPC_ObjDetL1Heap);
757 
758  /* initialize edma handles, unused handles will remain NULL to to memset above */
759  objDetInitParams.edmaHandle[DPC_OBJDET_DSP_EDMA_INSTANCE] = gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.edmaHandle;
760 
761  /* DPC Call-back config */
762  objDetInitParams.processCallBackCfg.processFrameBeginCallBackFxn =
763  MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_processFrameBeginCallBackFxn;
764  objDetInitParams.processCallBackCfg.processInterFrameBeginCallBackFxn =
765  MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_processInterFrameBeginCallBackFxn;
766 
767  memset ((void *)&dpmInitCfg, 0, sizeof(DPM_InitCfg));
768 
769  /* Setup the configuration: */
770  dpmInitCfg.socHandle = gMmwDssMCB.socHandle;
771  dpmInitCfg.ptrProcChainCfg = &gDPC_ObjectDetectionCfg;
772  dpmInitCfg.instanceId = DPC_OBJDET_DSP_INSTANCEID;
773  dpmInitCfg.domain = DPM_Domain_DISTRIBUTED;
774  dpmInitCfg.reportFxn = MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_reportFxn;
775  dpmInitCfg.arg = &objDetInitParams;
776  dpmInitCfg.argSize = sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_InitParams);
777 
778  /* Initialize the DPM Module: */
779  gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle = DPM_init (&dpmInitCfg, &errCode);
780  if (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle == NULL)
781  {
782  System_printf ("Error: Unable to initialize the DPM Module [Error: %d]\n", errCode);
783  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
784  return;
785  }
786 
787  /* Synchronization: This will synchronize the execution of the control module
788  * between the domains. This is a prerequiste and always needs to be invoked. */
789  while (1)
790  {
791  int32_t syncStatus;
792 
793  /* Get the synchronization status: */
794  syncStatus = DPM_synch (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle, &errCode);
795  if (syncStatus < 0)
796  {
797  /* Error: Unable to synchronize the framework */
798  System_printf ("Error: DPM Synchronization failed [Error code %d]\n", errCode);
799  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
800  return;
801  }
802  if (syncStatus == 1)
803  {
804  /* Synchronization acheived: */
805  break;
806  }
807  /* Sleep and poll again: */
808  Task_sleep(1);
809  }
810  System_printf ("Debug: DPM Module Sync is done\n");
811 
812  /* Launch the DPM Task */
813  Task_Params_init(&taskParams);
814  taskParams.priority = MMWDEMO_DPC_OBJDET_DPM_TASK_PRIORITY;
815  taskParams.stackSize = 4*1024;

845 int main (void)
846 {
847  Task_Params taskParams;
848  int32_t errCode;
849  SOC_Handle socHandle;
850  SOC_Cfg socCfg;
851 
852  /* Initialize and populate the demo MCB */
853  memset ((void*)&gMmwDssMCB, 0, sizeof(MmwDemo_DSS_MCB));
854 
855  /* Initialize the SOC confiugration: */
856  memset ((void *)&socCfg, 0, sizeof(SOC_Cfg));
857 
858  /* Populate the SOC configuration: */
859  socCfg.clockCfg = SOC_SysClock_BYPASS_INIT;
860 
861  /* Initialize the SOC Module: This is done as soon as the application is started
862  * to ensure that the MPU is correctly configured. */
863  socHandle = SOC_init (&socCfg, &errCode);
864  if (socHandle == NULL)
865  {
866  System_printf ("Error: SOC Module Initialization failed [Error code %d]\n", errCode);
867  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
868  return -1;
869  }
870 
871  gMmwDssMCB.socHandle = socHandle;
872 
873  /* Initialize the Task Parameters. */
874  Task_Params_init(&taskParams);
875  taskParams.stackSize = 4*1024;
876  gMmwDssMCB.initTaskHandle = Task_create(MmwDemo_dssInitTask, &taskParams, NULL);
877 
878  /* Start BIOS */
879  BIOS_start();
880  return 0;
881 }
